"$","p","0",{"className":"mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300","children":"South Africa's economy grew 0.4% quarter-on-quarter in Q4 2025 — seasonally adjusted and annualised — marking five consecutive quarters of expansion. Finance was the star performer, rising 1.4%. Manufacturing disappointed again, falling 0.6%."}],["$","p","1",{"className":"mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300","children":"For the full year 2025, GDP rose 1.1%. That is the highest annual growth rate since 2022, and better than the dismal 0.5% recorded in 2024 and the 0.7% in 2023."}]],["$","blockquote",null,{"className":"my-6 border-l-4 border-brand-400 pl-5","children":["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg font-medium italic leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200","children":["\"","Five consecutive quarters of positive growth — but \"positive\" masks how fragile that growth is.","\""]}]}],[["$","div",null,{"className":"my-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-900 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:gap-6","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex-shrink-0","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"font-mono text-4xl font-medium tabular-nums text-slate-900 dark:text-white","children":"0.4%"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-1 flex items-center gap-1.5","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-1 rounded-full px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium bg-brand-50 text-brand-700 dark:bg-brand-950/40 dark:text-brand-300","children":[["$","svg",null,{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":11,"height":11,"viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":2,"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","className":"lucide lucide-trending-up","children":[["$","polyline","126l90",{"points":"22 7 13.5 15.5 8.5 10.5 2 17"}],["$","polyline","kwv8wd",{"points":"16 7 22 7 22 13"}],"$undefined"]}],"0.1","pp"]}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xs text-slate-400","children":"from Q3 2025"}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"hidden h-12 w-px bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 sm:block"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex-1 min-w-0","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white","children":"GDP Growth Rate (Quarter-on-Quarter)"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 line-clamp-2","children":"South Africa's real GDP grew 0.4% quarter-on-quarter in Q4 2025, seasonally adjusted and annualised, above expectations of 0.3%. This marked the fifth consecutive quarter of expansion. Finance led growth (+1.4%), while manufacturing was the largest drag (-0.6%). For the full year 2025, GDP rose 1.1% — the strongest annual growth since 2022."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-2 text-xs text-slate-400","children":["Stats SA"," · Updated ","10 March 2026"]}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"my-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-900 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:gap-6","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex-shrink-0","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"font-mono text-4xl font-medium tabular-nums text-slate-900 dark:text-white","children":"1.1%"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-1 flex items-center gap-1.5","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-1 rounded-full px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium bg-brand-50 text-brand-700 dark:bg-brand-950/40 dark:text-brand-300","children":[["$","svg",null,{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":11,"height":11,"viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":2,"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","className":"lucide lucide-trending-up","children":[["$","polyline","126l90",{"points":"22 7 13.5 15.5 8.5 10.5 2 17"}],["$","polyline","kwv8wd",{"points":"16 7 22 7 22 13"}],"$undefined"]}],"0.6","pp"]}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xs text-slate-400","children":"from 2024 (0.5%)"}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"hidden h-12 w-px bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-800 sm:block"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex-1 min-w-0","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white","children":"GDP Annual Growth Rate"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-1 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 line-clamp-2","children":"South Africa's real GDP grew 1.1% for the full year 2025, the strongest annual rate since 2022. Growth was broad-based despite ongoing headwinds from high borrowing costs and slow global demand. Manufacturing registered its second year of negative growth; construction posted its ninth straight year of decline."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-2 text-xs text-slate-400","children":["Stats SA"," · Updated ","10 March 2026"]}]]}]]}]]]}],["$","section","not-enough",{"id":"not-enough","className":"mb-10 scroll-mt-24","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"heading-display mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white","children":"Why 1.1% is not enough"}],[["$","p","0",{"className":"mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300","children":"South Africa's population grows by roughly 1% per year. That means GDP must grow by at least 1% just to keep GDP per capita flat. At 1.1%, 2025 growth barely kept the country's head above water on a per-capita basis."}],["$","p","1",{"className":"mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300","children":"Most development economists argue South Africa needs sustained GDP growth of 5% or more to meaningfully reduce the 31% unemployment rate. The World Bank and IMF have similar benchmarks for the level of growth needed to reduce structural poverty."}],["$","p","2",{"className":"mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300","children":"South Africa has not grown above 3% since 2011 — more than a decade of sustained underperformance. Over that period, the economy grew at an average of around 1% per year in real terms."}]],"$undefined",[]]}],["$","section","what-held-back",{"id":"what-held-back","className":"mb-10 scroll-mt-24","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"heading-display mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white","children":"What held the economy back"}],[["$","p","0",{"className":"mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300","children":"The structural constraints on South African growth are well documented."}],["$","p","1",{"className":"mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300","children":"Load-shedding — scheduled electricity outages — inflicted billions of rands of economic damage each year from 2022 to 2024. The situation improved significantly from late 2024 as Eskom's maintenance programme bore fruit and new renewable energy capacity came online. But load-shedding has not been eliminated, and its legacy damage to business confidence and investment takes time to repair."}],["$","p","2",{"className":"mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300","children":"Logistics constraints also remain severe. Transnet, the state freight rail and ports company, has struggled with operational problems, theft of infrastructure, and deferred maintenance. Mining and agricultural exporters — the backbone of South Africa's current account — have been particularly hard hit."}],["$","p","3",{"className":"mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300","children":"Manufacturing recorded its second consecutive year of negative growth in 2025. Construction posted its ninth straight year of decline. Both sectors are critical for labour-intensive job creation."}]],"$undefined",[]]}],["$","section","bright-spots",{"id":"bright-spots","className":"mb-10 scroll-mt-24","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"heading-display mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white","children":"Bright spots and reasons for cautious optimism"}],[["$","p","0",{"className":"mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300","children":"Agriculture had a strong 2025, boosted by good rains and improved horticulture output. Finance and business services continued to expand. Tourism has recovered strongly from the post-pandemic trough."}],["$","p","1",{"className":"mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300","children":"Perhaps most significantly, South Africa was removed from the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) grey list in late 2024 — a development that should, over time, reduce compliance costs for South African businesses operating internationally and improve access to foreign capital."}],["$","p","2",{"className":"mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300","children":"Sovereign credit rating agencies have also taken note of improved fiscal discipline. Moody's and S&P both cited better-than-expected fiscal consolidation in their mid-2025 reviews, though South Africa's rating remains sub-investment grade."}]],"$undefined",[["$","div",null,{"className":"my-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-900 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:gap-6","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex-shrink-0","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"font-mono text-4xl font-medium tabular-nums text-slate-900 dark:text-white","children":"R7.67T"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-1 flex items-center gap-1.5","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-1 rounded-full px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium bg-brand-50 text-brand-700 dark:bg-brand-950/40 dark:text-brand-300","children":[["$","svg",null,{"xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":11,"height":11,"viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":2,"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","className":"lucide lucide-trending-up","children":[["$",